Use the standard library
This is how to sort_third of l:
   Remember that thirds is []
   Remember that n is l's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that r is remainder of i and 3
      When r is 0, then:
         Add thirds to item i in l
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   Remember that thirds is bubble_sort of thirds
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that t is 0
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that r is remainder of i and 3
      When r is 0, then:
         Add result to item t in thirds
         Increase t
      But, if not:
         Add result to item i in l
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> sort_third of [1, 2, 3]
[1, 2, 3]
>>> sort_third of [5, 6, 3, 4, 8, 9, 2]
[2, 6, 3, 4, 8, 9, 5]
>>> sort_third of [1, 2, 3]
[1, 2, 3]